  displayName: Kapre
  description: Typically described as a towering giant dwelling in old trees, the
    kapre is tied to deep forests and enduring natural spaces. Folk narratives portray
    it as territorial yet not always malicious, with behavior shaped by respect,
    provocation, and boundary crossing. As a mythic figure, the kapre frequently
    symbolizes ancient presence and the warning that sacred landscapes are never
    truly empty.
